Learning **Azure** or **AWS DevOps** from fundamentals—especially in detail—requires a structured approach because 
DevOps combines **development**, **operations**, **automation**, and **cloud platforms**. 

Below is a detailed step-by-step roadmap to help you learn **Azure or AWS DevOps** from scratch:

✅ **Step-by-Step Guide to Learn Azure/AWS DevOps from Fundamentals**
************************************************
# 🧭 **Step 1: Understand DevOps Fundamentals**
************************************************
Before jumping into Azure or AWS, you need a solid foundation in **DevOps concepts**:

* What is DevOps?
* CI/CD (Continuous Integration / Continuous Deployment)
* Infrastructure as Code (IaC)
* Version control (e.g., Git)
* Agile & Scrum basics
* Monitoring & Logging

📘 Resources:

* Free: [Microsoft DevOps Docs](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/devops/)
* Book: *The Phoenix Project* by Gene Kim
* Course: Udemy – DevOps Fundamentals

*****************************************
# ☁️ **Step 2: Choose a Cloud Platform**
*****************************************
You can pick **Azure** or **AWS** to start. Both are popular; the choice depends on your interest or job market in your region.

**🔷 Azure DevOps Learning Path**
*****************************************
# 🪜 Step 3A: Learn Azure Basics
*****************************************
* Azure Subscription & Free Tier
* Resource Groups, Virtual Machines, Storage
* Azure CLI, PowerShell

🎓 Resources:

* Microsoft Learn: [Azure Fundamentals](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/training/paths/azure-fundamentals/)
* Certification: **AZ-900** (Azure Fundamentals)

*****************************************
# 🔧 Step 4A: Learn Azure DevOps Services
*****************************************
* Azure Repos (Git)
* Azure Pipelines (CI/CD)
* Azure Boards (Agile Project Management)
* Azure Artifacts
* Azure Test Plans

🎓 Resources:
* Microsoft Learn: [Azure DevOps Learning Path](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/training/paths/get-started-azure-devops/)
* Project: Build CI/CD pipeline for a .NET or Node.js app

*****************************************
# ☸️ Step 5A: Infrastructure as Code (IaC) in Azure
*****************************************
* ARM Templates
* **Terraform with Azure**
* Azure Bicep (optional)

*********************************
 **🟧 AWS DevOps Learning Path**
*********************************

*****************************************
# 🪜 Step 3B: Learn AWS Basics
*****************************************
* AWS Free Tier Setup
* EC2, S3, IAM, VPC Basics
* AWS CLI, IAM Roles

🎓 Resources:

* AWS Skill Builder: [AWS Cloud Practitioner](https://explore.skillbuilder.aws/learn/course/external/view/elearning/134/aws-cloud-practitioner-essentials)
* Certification: **CLF-C02 (AWS Cloud Practitioner)**


*****************************************
# 🔧 Step 4B: Learn AWS DevOps Tools
*****************************************
* AWS CodeCommit (Git Repo)
* AWS CodeBuild (CI)
* AWS CodePipeline (CD)
* AWS CodeDeploy
* CloudWatch (Monitoring)

🎓 Resources:

* AWS DevOps Engineer Path: [AWS DevOps Learning](https://aws.amazon.com/devops/learn/)
* Project: Deploy app using CodePipeline from GitHub to EC2

*****************************************
# ☸️ Step 5B: Infrastructure as Code (IaC) in AWS
*****************************************
* AWS CloudFormation
* **Terraform with AWS**

*****************************************
 🛠️ **Step 6: Tools & Technologies to Learn (Common for Both)**
*****************************************
* **Git** & GitHub/GitLab/Bitbucket
* **Docker** – Containerization
* **Kubernetes** (basics)
* **Terraform** – Infrastructure as Code
* **Ansible** (optional)
* **Jenkins** (optional but valuable)

*****************************************
 📈 Step 7: Practice with Real Projects
*****************************************
* Create CI/CD pipeline for a web app (Node.js, Python, or Java)
* Deploy containerized apps using Docker on Azure/AWS
* Use Terraform to provision cloud infrastructure
* Set up monitoring and alerts (CloudWatch or Azure Monitor)

*****************************************
 🎓 Step 8: Get Certified
*****************************************
# Azure:
* **AZ-400**: Designing and Implementing Microsoft DevOps Solutions

# AWS:
* **AWS Certified DevOps Engineer – Professional**
These validate your skills and are highly valued by employers.

*****************************************
 🧪 Step 9: Hands-On Practice Platforms
*****************************************
* [Microsoft Learn Sandbox](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/training/)
* [AWS Free Tier](https://aws.amazon.com/free/)
* [Katacoda](https://www.katacoda.com/)
* [GitHub Projects](https://github.com)

